<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="description" content="Request stuff to borrow">
<meta name="robots" content="noodp">
</head>

  <div class="col-xs-12" style="padding-bottom:1%;">
    <h4><%="Step 2 of 2: Borrow away, #{@signup_parent.email}!"%></h4>
    <h5 style="font-size:90%; font-style:italic">
      Click to 
      <%= link_to 'lend stuff', @signup_parent.inventories.count > 0 ? manage_inventory_path : new_inventory_path, { style: 'color:#428bca'}%>
    </h5>

    <p>Woohoo, now you get to tell us what you need! Please keep in mind:</p>
    <ul style="font-size:90%;">
    <li><b>Once you submit</b> we'll send an email to all the lenders who have the item(s) you want <b>in your county</b> (note that most of our lenders are in San Francisco), and connect you with whoever 'accepts' first.
    <li>If you request multiple items, it is likely that you'll have to coordinate with multiple lenders</li>
    <li>We recommend submitting a request <b>1-2 weeks in advance</b> with an extra <b>"buffer" day</b> on each end. It may be difficult for lenders to respond to same day requests</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
        	
  <%= render "layouts/requestform" %>
  <form action="" method="POST">
      <script
        src="https://checkout.stripe.com/checkout.js" class="stripe-button"
        data-key="pk_test_6pRNASCoBOKtIshFeQd4XMUh"
        data-amount="<%= @signup_parent.inventories.count*10 %>"
        data-name="Demo Site"
        data-description="<%= @signup_parent.inventories.count%> items (<%= @signup_parent.inventories.count*10 %>)"
        data-image="/128x128.png">
      </script>
  </form>